  <Entries>
    <Entry>
      <ID>1</ID>
      <DefaultText>Lantry stops his stride, darting his hands about his bandolier and belt as he softly mouths off a mental inventory of his inks and quills. When at last assured his possessions are in place, he looks up at you with a smile.</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>2</ID>
      <DefaultText>"What might I do for you?"</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>5</ID>
      <DefaultText>"Who are you?"</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>6</ID>
      <DefaultText>"If you're going to be traveling with me, I need to know more about you."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>7</ID>
      <DefaultText>"We'll talk more later."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>8</ID>
      <DefaultText>"Tell me about the Sages."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>10</ID>
      <DefaultText>"Apologies if I didn't properly introduce myself earlier. All my works are written under the name [url=glossary:sage]Sage[/url] Lantry of the [url=glossary:vellum citadel]Vellum Citadel[/url] - but outside of proper citations, 'Lantry' will suffice."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>12</ID>
      <DefaultText>"What do you know of the [url=glossary:vellum citadel]Vellum Citadel[/url]?"</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>14</ID>
      <DefaultText>"Indeed - I've a finite appetite for discussing myself, and I'm more than sated. Let us press onward."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>15</ID>
      <DefaultText>"For hundreds of years, the Sages have been devoted to the collection and preservation of knowledge. We are scholars, bookmakers, archivists, and students of the mystic and the mundane alike. The wisest of our guild - not that I truly belong in that category - are versed in sigils and spellcraft."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>16</ID>
      <DefaultText>"Or that's at least how it used to be. With the destruction of the [url=glossary:vellum citadel]Vellum Citadel[/url], the Sages have been scattered to the winds. There were once more Sages than I could name - many have died or been taken prisoner by [url=glossary:kyros]Kyros[/url]' forces."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>20</ID>
      <DefaultText>"An understandable request. Let's see... born in Sunder, no kids - what few longings of fatherly love I've got in my heart are satisfied by taking care of carrier birds. Learned my sigils and spells about thirty years back, and being able to defend myself has opened a life of field study - and haven't grown tired of the wandering just yet."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>21</ID>
      <DefaultText>"I've written on all manner of subjects - magic, birds, language, geometry... but my main focus has been chronicling. I find there's no finer pursuit than recording the events of our times. There will always be legends of what happened - someone ought to be making note of the real thing."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>22</ID>
      <DefaultText>Lantry scowls, his writing hand becomes unusually still. "I once felt a rush of pride at that name - now it's a blight on our reputation."

Lantry clears his throat, reasserting his smile. "The [url=glossary:vellum citadel]Vellum Citadel[/url] was a beautiful sanctuary of parchment and ink. We had amassed knowledge from the Northern Empire to the coast of the Tiers. It would take a score of lifetimes to learn all the Citadel could teach you."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>23</ID>
      <DefaultText>"But the Sages in charge of the [url=glossary:vellum citadel]Vellum Citadel[/url] thought themselves above [url=glossary:kyros]Kyros[/url]' rules. The Overlord learned the Sages were copying and spreading lies and forbidden knowledge."

"[url=glossary:kyros]Kyros[/url] put an end to life at the Citadel with his [url=glossary:edict]Edict[/url] of Fire." Lantry stops, putting a hand to his face. "All that knowledge set aflame..."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>25</ID>
      <DefaultText>"When we bind books, we bind them to last - our most important tomes were warded against fire and other maladies."

Lantry scowls. "So many of the books remain intact as the shelf and floor melt away. I suppose it's still there, if you want to brave danger and certain death for it. There is good reason they call it the [url=glossary:burning library]Burning Library[/url] now."

He shrugs.</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>26</ID>
      <DefaultText>"Tell me about your work with the oathbreakers."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>27</ID>
      <DefaultText>"The [url=glossary:vendrien guard]Vendrien Guard[/url] has several noble-born in their ranks, and they know their letters - problem is, they've come from nobles houses scattered across the Realms - each with their own private script. That's where the Sages and I come in - between us, we're familiar enough with all the regional scripts to translate and coordinate."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>28</ID>
      <DefaultText>"How'd you wind up here in [url=glossary:vendrien's well]Vendrien's Well[/url]?"</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>30</ID>
      <DefaultText>"When the [url=glossary:vellum citadel]Vellum Citadel[/url] was set aflame by [url=glossary:kyros]Kyros[/url]' [url=glossary:edict]Edict[/url], I fled as fast as my knees would carry me. Every direction seemed a bad idea, but heading to [url=glossary:vendrien's well]Vendrien's Well[/url] seemed the least suicidal option... mind you, I was laboring under the misconception that the [url=glossary:vendrien guard]Vendrien Guard[/url] had surrendered, and the fighting in the valley had stopped."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>31</ID>
      <DefaultText>"Ah yes - Seventh of Sparring - that's when I crossed the mountains. That would be... two days? Three days after the [url=glossary:vendrien guard]Vendrien Guard[/url] jettisoned their surrender and claimed the citadel in the valley."

"The [url=glossary:vendrien guard]Vendrien Guard[/url] nabbed me and several other Sages moving through the valley. The other Sages were sympathetic to the [url=glossary:vendrien guard]Vendrien Guard[/url]. As for me, I just agreed so as not to get everyone killed. I think defying the Overlord is a really slow and stupid form of suicide."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>32</ID>
      <DefaultText>"But translating is child's play, so I... might have helped out a bit more. The old citadel at the center of the valley is a crumbling affair and there's no time for proper construction - seemed a crime not to put my magic to work."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>33</ID>
      <DefaultText>"Fatebinder, don't let me disappear in some [url=glossary:disfavored]Disfavored[/url] holding cell or, worse, be thrown to the Chorus! Others in my guild do not see the wisdom of [url=glossary:kyros]Kyros[/url]' rule, but I do! Please, you have the authority to take me into your own custody."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>34</ID>
      <DefaultText>Trigger Conv Node 34</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>35</ID>
      <DefaultText>"Well much of the parchment was weathered, but I could make out the important parts of the text. The note makes mention of a meeting spot west of Tripnettle."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>36</ID>
      <DefaultText>"So the old [url=glossary:sage]Sage[/url] knows his words after all? I'd ask that you travel ahead and see if you can't get this Captain Florian to yield to the Chorus. They will strike at first sight of a Chorus gang, but perhaps they will parlay if yours is the face they see."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>37</ID>
      <DefaultText>Looking first at his left arm, then his right, he reads through the assorted notes inked across his skin.</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>38</ID>
      <DefaultText>"What did you learn of their plans in your time there?"</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>39</ID>
      <DefaultText>"So you provided military aid to the oathbreakers?"</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>40</ID>
      <DefaultText>"What else can you tell me about the oathbreakers and their forces?"</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>41</ID>
      <DefaultText>"Let me ask about something else."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>42</ID>
      <DefaultText>"It won't surprise you to know their strategy is largely non-existent. They cling to the hope that their example will inspire others in the Tiers to come to the valley and join the cause. The recent inaction between the Archons has emboldened them - some even think the Archons FEAR the [url=glossary:vendrien guard]Vendrien Guard[/url]... I'm sure they have it quite wrong."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>43</ID>
      <DefaultText>"How did you wind up a prisoner of the Chorus?"</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>44</ID>
      <DefaultText>"I had to send some missives and that meant getting to a clearing where my terns and doves might find me. The patrol with me was ambushed by the [url=glossary:scarlet chorus]Scarlet Chorus[/url]. I tried to flee the scene but some youngster tackled me and well... out of one fire, into another - that's been a running theme this year."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>45</ID>
      <DefaultText>"When the servant of the Archon of Justice asks me that question, I can't help but assume it's the antecedent to some sort of punishment. I can't deny that I assisted the oathbreakers, but the alternative was to starve in a cell and maybe lose my head. I realize this is an offense to the Overlord, but it's not like I increased their odds of winning in any significant way."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>47</ID>
      <DefaultText>"At highest count, earlier in the year, they numbered over four hundred - their ranks swollen by soldiers of Haven and Azure that survived the war. They are a dying breed, these oathbreakers - most in the Tiers have finally come to realize that [url=glossary:kyros]Kyros[/url] has already won."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>48</ID>
      <DefaultText>"And before you ask, as connoisseur of the inevitable, I have made my peace with the Overlord and bow to his might."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>49</ID>
      <DefaultText>"Aside from that... I don't know... I practice centering stance, draw portraits, make my own inks, and have a sharp aversion to autobiography. I'm about as boring as watching coral grow."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>51</ID>
      <DefaultText>"The [url=glossary:vendrien guard]Vendrien Guard[/url] surrendered back in 429 - and while a lot of them were conscripted in the Chorus, three of the leaders - Captains Arri, Matani, and Florian, never turned themselves in. Instead, they hid in the valley, gathering up what resources they could until they could challenge the local garrison."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>53</ID>
      <DefaultText>"Who leads the School?"</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>54</ID>
      <DefaultText>"The Sages would not bow to [url=glossary:kyros]Kyros[/url], yet you do..."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>55</ID>
      <DefaultText>"True... my peers can grasp many abstract concepts, but on the subject of hopeless wars, their stupidity rises to idiotic splendor. The Sages believed themselves the mightiest magical guild in the Tiers - and they could even back that claim... but they mistook being the best for being a match for [url=glossary:kyros]Kyros[/url]. How it is so many can study so much history and learn so little?"</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>56</ID>
      <DefaultText>"I've studied [url=glossary:kyros]Kyros[/url] and the Archons in great detail - enough so that I am no longer blinded by fear of their magic, nor by envy of their special gifts. To my mind, it seems like nonsense to bow to a mere king or queen when one could serve [url=glossary:kyros]Kyros[/url], the living embodiment of rulership."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>57</ID>
      <DefaultText>"I keep learning more names of those who died during the [url=glossary:edict]Edict[/url] of Fire, so my information could be obsolete... but with [url=glossary:sage]Sage[/url] Crevnik incinerated, [url=glossary:sage]Sage[/url] Renata would be the current provost. And if she dies... well fuck, thanks to all the recent deaths, maybe I'll be next in line. Let's archive that away under things to worry about later."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>58</ID>
      <DefaultText>"In truth, there isn't much guild left to lead. Our library fortress is in ashes, our membership in disarray... and it doesn't help that we have something of a spotty reputation here in the Tiers... fear of magic being something of a local specialty."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>59</ID>
      <DefaultText>"Let me ask about something else."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>60</ID>
      <DefaultText>"What's your role in the guild?"</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>61</ID>
      <DefaultText>"I'm one of the chief writers of the Chronicle - it's our attempt to record the truth of all things in their proper sequence. It's the ongoing lifework of generations of Sages - and I have the honor of witnessing history and having my vantage point be a matter of record."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>62</ID>
      <DefaultText>"Five tomes are bound by my hand, and I've trained letters and numbers to nearly a thousand minds. But most of all that work went up in flames... I'm sure I'm not the only person in the Tiers wondering where life will go after these messy years."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>63</ID>
      <DefaultText>"Intent matters. You were doing what you needed to survive."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>64</ID>
      <DefaultText>[Glare silently.]</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>65</ID>
      <DefaultText>"Personal survival does not exempt one from observing the laws of [url=glossary:kyros]Kyros[/url]."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>66</ID>
      <DefaultText>"Well... I trust my future actions will show I mean to be of service, not a source of problems."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>67</ID>
      <DefaultText>"Of course, a criminal can rationalize any debased act with the excuse of self-survival. I did not mean to imply such disregard for the Overlords laws."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>68</ID>
      <DefaultText>"You're offering to come with me? Why?"</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>69</ID>
      <DefaultText>"Something's amiss. There's a lot of fight in you for an old scholar. Now you're offering to join this expedition..."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>70</ID>
      <DefaultText>"How about you just tell me where it is, I don't need you tagging along."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>71</ID>
      <DefaultText>"I've met Sages every bit as cutthroat as hardened gang bosses. They act the part of doddering scribes, but don't let that fool you." </DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>72</ID>
      <DefaultText>"Smart for someone your age to be so mistrusting. But I'm not with the oathbreakers, if that's what you're fishing at. I worked for them under duress, but I've no love of them. I'm not about to pledge to the Chorus, and the [url=glossary:disfavored]Disfavored[/url] wouldn't have me. Still, I consider myself a [url=glossary:kyros]Kyros[/url]-fearing vassal of the Overlord's empire all the same."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>73</ID>
      <DefaultText>"Because the alternative is... what? Living here with these illiterate brutes? My old study is under a river of fire and there's no family missing me."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>74</ID>
      <DefaultText>"Besides, I'd much rather chronicle the Binder that twice proclaimed an [url=glossary:edict]Edict[/url] of [url=glossary:kyros]Kyros[/url]. I'd be a fool to let someone else write your story."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>75</ID>
      <DefaultText>"For as long as I've been a [url=glossary:sage]Sage[/url] I've been trained to defend myself. We don't spend all our time binding books and sketching wildlife, just most of it. For centuries we've been in a quiet war with the School of Tides and the School of Wild Wrath. You can't travel alone as much as I do and not know the bronze dance."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>76</ID>
      <DefaultText>"I'd make myself useful! I'm not half as fragile and cowardly as I look, and I know a thing or two about... well, a lot. I would ask you to reconsider - I can't very well just loaf about here with the Chorus."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>77</ID>
      <DefaultText>"You want to chronicle me?"</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>78</ID>
      <DefaultText>"Fine. If you are so eager, come with me."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>79</ID>
      <DefaultText>"The Chorus wouldn't mind. You have most of your teeth - a pretty mouth like yours will make you a favorite here in the camp."

"The gangs aren't picky." </DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>80</ID>
      <DefaultText>"My uh... my point exactly."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>81</ID>
      <DefaultText>"Well of course. Even if the [url=glossary:burning library]Burning Library[/url] is never rebuilt, our work to chronicle the days and events needn't cease. And you're a noteworthy player in this whole war - I can't think of another living Fatebinder that has been twice given the honor of proclamation."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>82</ID>
      <DefaultText>"Swear fealty to me, and I will let you leave this place with me."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>83</ID>
      <DefaultText>"Sorry, you're on your own."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>84</ID>
      <DefaultText>"I understand. Thank you for securing my freedom. I'll sketch you map to where these oathbreakers should be lurking."

He unfurls a delicately drawn map of the valley and inks out a route from your current location. Based on this information, it should not be hard to find.</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>85</ID>
      <DefaultText>"Good luck on your mission to Tripnettle. For now, I bid you farewell. I do so hope our paths cross once again, I still owe you for my freedom, after all."

With a gracious bow, the old man smiles, and turns to leave.</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>86</ID>
      <DefaultText>"Splendid! You won't be disappointed. "</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>88</ID>
      <DefaultText>"If that is your price, I will pay it. I, [url=glossary:sage]Sage[/url] Lantry of the School of Ink and Quill, do pledge my services and skein to the Fatebinder, and by extension, to the Court of [url=glossary:tunon]Tunon[/url]."

He dips into a steep bow, before rising with a solemn smile.</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>89</ID>
      <DefaultText>"I know I may seem old and frail, but I know how to step lightly and how not to get killed - really, I won't slow you down. Lead the way, and let me know if I can be of service."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>90</ID>
      <DefaultText>"Slow down. Introductions might be in order."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>91</ID>
      <DefaultText>"My apologies, guess we skipped past that part. I'm [url=glossary:sage]Sage[/url] Lantry, formerly of the [url=glossary:vellum citadel]Vellum Citadel[/url] and now of... well, of nowhere, I guess."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>92</ID>
      <DefaultText>"Are we done here? Let's hightail it to Tripnettle. If your new pet doesn't behave himself along the way, I'm not above clipping his ears."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>93</ID>
      <DefaultText>"We should make haste to Tripnettle. A warrior like Florian will butcher these Chorus whelps, but he'll be no match for me."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>94</ID>
      <DefaultText>"Good luck on your mission to Tripnettle. For now, I'll bid you a pleasant farewell. I heard one of the Fatebinders made alcohols completely legal in [url=glossary:lethian's crossing]Lethian's Crossing[/url], so if you find yourself there, I owe you a drink or seven for your kindness."

With a gracious bow, the old man smiles, and turns to leave.</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>95</ID>
      <DefaultText>"So you're an expert with fortifications?"</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>96</ID>
      <DefaultText>"Hardly. But I am an expert on Preservation magics. The same cantrips we use at the School of Ink and Quill to preserve our manuscripts against worms and decay are, in principle, as applicable to stone as they are to parchment... plus or minus some improvisation."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>99</ID>
      <DefaultText>"Fatebinder! Still kicking, I see?"

Looking sleepless and disheveled, Lantry wipes his forehead, leaving an ink stain across his brow as he does.</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>100</ID>
      <DefaultText>"So... word has it, [url=glossary:kyros]Kyros[/url]' magic has sealed the mountain passes - no use trying to leave this pleasant little valley. Least not until the [url=glossary:edict]Edict[/url] is resolved... or until it comes to pass and renders irrelevant all future plans."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>101</ID>
      <DefaultText>"Don't suppose you've reconsidered the notion of having an elderly twit shadowing you and taking notes? I assure you, I'm harmless, or at least mostly harmless."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>102</ID>
      <DefaultText>"So what's your plan? Just loaf here?"</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>103</ID>
      <DefaultText>"Where will you go when the valley is no longer sealed?"</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>104</ID>
      <DefaultText>"Perhaps another time."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>105</ID>
      <DefaultText>"The most interesting things currently  happening in the Tiers are taking place here in the valley. I figure I'll shadow the armies and make note of the how the next few days unfold. It would be a shame for the week's events to exist only as rumor and gossip - someone ought to record the real story."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>106</ID>
      <DefaultText>"Pondering that as we speak. I'm debating going northeast or southeast, I would like to see the Edicts of Stone and Storms, respectively, and try to note them in detail. Not sure who'll be around to read my notes or care, but I can't let these wonders go unstudied."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>107</ID>
      <DefaultText>"I know a polite brush off where I hear it. Good day, Fatebinder."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>108</ID>
      <DefaultText>"Fine. If you are so eager, come with me."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>109</ID>
      <DefaultText>"Swear fealty to me, and I will let you leave this place with me."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>110</ID>
      <DefaultText>"Splendid! You won't be disappointed. "</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>111</ID>
      <DefaultText>"If that is your price, I will pay it. I, [url=glossary:sage]Sage[/url] Lantry of the School of Ink and Quill, do pledge my services and skein to the Fatebinder, and by extension, to the Court of [url=glossary:tunon]Tunon[/url]."

He dips into a steep bow, before rising with a solemn smile.</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>112</ID>
      <DefaultText>"I know I may seem old and frail, but I know how to step lightly and how not to get killed - really, I won't slow you down. Lead the way, and let me know if I can be of service."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>113</ID>
      <DefaultText>"Tell me about your magic."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>114</ID>
      <DefaultText>"Oh, I don't much like to brag about things like that."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>115</ID>
      <DefaultText>"You said you'd teach me a thing or two about magic. That happens now."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>116</ID>
      <DefaultText>"Ah yes, yes yes yes - I did promise you that. Well... this isn't exactly a quiet classroom, but I suppose it will suffice. Before I start... are you sure we have time, what with the [url=glossary:edict]Edict[/url] and all? We can always do this later."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>117</ID>
      <DefaultText>"We'll start with first principles. When mending wounds and easing pain, we invoke the magic of the Orphan Midwife, Archon of Rebirth. By invoking her sigil, we channel her mastery, however briefly, through our hands. Now, trace the sigil, following the lines in the order I sketched them."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>118</ID>
      <DefaultText>"No time like the present."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>119</ID>
      <DefaultText>"Time is of the essence, this can wait."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>120</ID>
      <DefaultText>[Follow his instructions.]</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>121</ID>
      <DefaultText>"What can you tell me about this Archon of Rebirth?"</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>122</ID>
      <DefaultText>"On second thought, can we do this later?"</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>123</ID>
      <DefaultText>"The [url=glossary:edict]Edict[/url] of Execution is about to kill everyone in the valley... it does make a bit of sense to save this for later."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>124</ID>
      <DefaultText>Rummaging through his satchels, the [url=glossary:sage]Sage[/url] produces a long quill and a crumpled piece of parchment. With seven quick strokes of the quill, he inks a pattern on the page.</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>125</ID>
      <DefaultText>"Since this isn't your first cantrip, I'll move a little quickly, but I think you can keep up."

Lantry walks you through countless repetitions of the signing the mystic sigil. For hours, you wave your hand in the air to no effect, until at last, you sign the pattern in the air and feel a rush of power through your veins.</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>126</ID>
      <DefaultText>"Didn't realize you gave a care about your history. Well, the Orphan Midwife was born in 160, bowed to [url=glossary:kyros]Kyros[/url] in 201. They say where she walked, plants would sprout, the sick would grow vigorous... she'd also send most folks into fits of rage and animals into heat - she sounds like quite a riot."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>127</ID>
      <DefaultText>"We know her magic by way of one of her first disciples, who migrated to the Tiers in 222 to spread her wisdom - an act that happened to be illegal under [url=glossary:kyros]Kyros[/url]' law. For that and a host of other transgressions, the Orphan Midwife has been imprisoned for over a century, or so the story goes."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>128</ID>
      <DefaultText>[Follow along.] "Trust me, I'm a natural with this sort of thing."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>129</ID>
      <DefaultText>"Youth and confidence - where you find one, you often find the other... and let me tell you one thing I know for sure - hubris and magic don't mix. Still, if you're eager to learn, that's music to my ears."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>130</ID>
      <DefaultText>"... and so if you need to heal pain as opposed to purge an infection, you'd move your hand like so. But you know... that's enough for now and I think the rest you can figure out on your own."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>131</ID>
      <DefaultText>"Not asking you to brag, I'm asking you to tell me what you can do."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>132</ID>
      <DefaultText>"Can you teach me anything?"</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>133</ID>
      <DefaultText>"Let's speak of something else."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>134</ID>
      <DefaultText>"Sure? I can show you how to blend your own inks, train birds to think you're their mom, how to turn a goat into parchment... but I'm sure you'd prefer to learn some magic."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>135</ID>
      <DefaultText>"If the School of Ink and Quill still mattered, I'd maybe be more tight-lipped but... if we're going to travel together, you should know how to mend wounds, especially if I'm killed."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>136</ID>
      <DefaultText>"I know the [url=glossary:edict]Edict[/url] still looms, but if you have a few hours, I could show you the basics of healing magic - or at least how I learned it."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>137</ID>
      <DefaultText>"No time like the present."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
