      <ID>150</ID>
      <DefaultText>"We know her magic by way of one of her first disciples, who migrated to the Tiers in 222 to spread her wisdom - an act that happened to be illegal under [url=glossary:kyros]Kyros[/url]' law. For that and a host of other transgressions, the Orphan Midwife has been imprisoned for over a century, or so the story goes."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>151</ID>
      <DefaultText>"My major areas of focus have been Preservation, Concealment, and Healing - arts that have served me well in this newfound life as a peripatetic prey animal."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>152</ID>
      <DefaultText>"The Sages study all kinds of magic, but as a Chronicler, I wanted magic that would help me see more, archive more, protect objects of historical value. Seeing as I feel like an old relic in need of some protection, my skills suit me well."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>153</ID>
      <DefaultText>"So you won't be a parchment weight during a fight... good to know."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>154</ID>
      <DefaultText>"And your little quill dagger... just for decoration?"</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>155</ID>
      <DefaultText>"Do you think I'm an idiot? Who sent you to kill me?"</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>156</ID>
      <DefaultText>"Oh no, I'd like to think I'm worth at least three or four angry peasants in a fight."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>157</ID>
      <DefaultText>"Well I mean... Sages always need to have a quill handy so, it just sort of... blends into the ensemble on a casual glance. And the customary term is 'bladed remex' but who's keeping track?"</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>158</ID>
      <DefaultText>"You have it all wrong, Fatebinder. Now I did have orders to spy on the Archons' servants but that comes from a now-fallen School. If someone wanted you dead, I'm the wrong agent for that sort of work."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>159</ID>
      <DefaultText>[Glare silently.]</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>160</ID>
      <DefaultText>"I know the area, and I suggest we go at once. I'll show you the way - I'm eager to be far from the stench of this camp."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>161</ID>
      <DefaultText>"I would be honored to learn a little of what you know."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>162</ID>
      <DefaultText>"Don't suppose you've reconsidered the notion of having an elderly twit shadowing you and taking notes? I assure you, I'm harmless, or at least mostly harmless."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
